text: The by-election for Lyttelton in 1873 was a by-election held in the electorate during the 5th Parliament of New Zealand, on 19 May 1873. It was held because John Thomas Peacock was appointed to the New Zealand Legislative Council. Peacock's brother-in-law, Henry Richard Webb, won the election. ==Results== ==References== Category:By-elections in New Zealand Category:1873 elections in New Zealand Category:Politics of Christchurch Category:1870s in Christchurch Category:History of Christchurch Category:Lyttelton, New Zealand
